answers.body_markdown:
You are mixing different types of connection. To connect to RMI services you should pair this server code:

    Registry reg = LocateRegistry.createRegistry(port);
    reg.rebind(&quot;Service&quot;, myHello);

with client code:

    Registry reg = LocateRegistry.getRegistry(port);
    Blah stub = (Blah) reg.lookup(&quot;Service&quot;);

Alternatively if you have started `rmiregistry` by:

    set CLASSPATH=/path/to/your-client.jar
    rmiregistry &lt;port&gt;

Then this server code:

    Naming.rebind(&quot;rmi://&quot;+hostname+&quot;:&quot;+port+&quot;/&quot;+name, stub);

is matched by client code:

    Blah stub = (Blah) Naming.lookup(&quot;rmi://&quot;+hostname+&quot;:&quot;+port+&quot;/&quot;+name);

