You could use [Math.random()][1] instead of the Random class. Math.random() returns a double between 0 and 1. So the only thing you have to do is multiply the result of Math.random() with N. The next number would be N minus your result from the subtraction of N and the previous result.

    final int N = 20;
    final int result0 = (int) (Math.random() * N);
    final int result1 = (int) (Math.random() * (N - result0));
    final int result2 = N - result0 - result1;

EDIT: You could than choose the first, second and third parameter randomly too. 

