    		new InterestRateCalculator().run();

This line does two things.  It creates an instance of the InterestRateCalculator class and it executes the run method of the class.

It may seem strange now, but getting away from static methods and static fields allows you to create complex Java applications with many, many classes.  You should learn this now, while you&#39;re writing simple applications.

